In order to describe exposures, sensitivity and potential impacts in the SMDHU population from climate-sensitive health vulnerability categories, data was required for:
 
  

current and projected local climate (i.e., temperature and precipitation);
  
  

current and projected population distributions;
  
  

current and historic prevalence of climate-sensitive health outcomes; and
  
  

prevalence of behaviors that modify the sensitivity to these climate sensitive health outcomes (e.g., sun safety behaviors).
